The problem of string matching with variable length gaps is a fundamental problem in computational biology, which suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. The paper also presents a new algorithm with time and space complexities, which indicates that it may belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) category. The algorithm achieves a logarithmic factor in the number of strings in the pattern, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) category. The problem involves searching for substrings in a larger string, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) category. Finally, the paper presents algorithms for finding and encoding the positions of all strings in the pattern, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) category.
